oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Pregnancy Rates of Recipient Animals Following Administration of a Prostaglandin F2α Receptor Antagonist to Collection Medium during Embryo Recovery
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Prado, T. M.
Scenna, F. N.
Edwards, J. L.
Roper, D. A.
Schrick, F. N.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: PGF2α receptor
embryo development
collection medium
pregnancy rates
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Previous research has indicated that addition of a PGF2α receptor (FPr) antagonist to culture medium prevented the detrimental action of PGF2α on embryo development. The aim of this study was to evaluate addition of a FPr antagonist to collection medium on pregnancy rates of recipient animals.
